## 4. Results and Findings

### 4.1 Model Performance Comparison

#### 4.1.1 Overall Accuracy Results

Table 1 summarizes the accuracy of all three models under both preprocessing strategies:

**Table 1: Model Accuracy Comparison**

| Model | Strategy 1 (Imputation) | Strategy 2 (Unknown Category) | Difference |
|-------|-------------------------|-------------------------------|------------|
| Decision Tree | 88.54% | 88.88% | +0.34% |
| Linear Regression | 90.15% | 90.13% | -0.02% |
| **Random Forest** | **90.99%** ⭐ | **90.91%** | -0.08% |

**Key Findings:**
1. Random Forest achieves the best performance (90.99%)
2. Strategy differences are minimal (<0.34% across all models)
3. Linear Regression surprisingly outperforms Decision Tree

#### 4.1.2 Detailed Performance Metrics

**Table 2: Random Forest Performance (Strategy 1)**

| Metric | Class 0 (No) | Class 1 (Yes) | Weighted Avg |
|--------|--------------|---------------|--------------|
| Precision | 0.93 | 0.68 | 0.90 |
| Recall | 0.97 | 0.45 | 0.91 |
| F1-Score | 0.95 | 0.54 | 0.90 |
| Support | 7,265 | 971 | 8,236 |

**Table 3: Linear Regression Performance (Strategy 1)**

| Metric | Class 0 (No) | Class 1 (Yes) | Weighted Avg |
|--------|--------------|---------------|--------------|
| Precision | 0.91 | 0.68 | 0.89 |
| Recall | 0.98 | 0.32 | 0.90 |
| F1-Score | 0.95 | 0.43 | 0.89 |
| R² Score | - | - | 0.345 |

**Table 4: Decision Tree Performance (Strategy 1)**

| Metric | Class 0 (No) | Class 1 (Yes) | Weighted Avg |
|--------|--------------|---------------|--------------|
| Precision | 0.93 | 0.51 | 0.89 |
| Recall | 0.94 | 0.51 | 0.89 |
| F1-Score | 0.94 | 0.51 | 0.89 |

**Analysis:**
- All models show strong performance on majority class (No)
- Minority class (Yes) remains challenging for all models
- Random Forest provides the best balance between precision and recall for "Yes" class

